 @{" " link "'#toc0'/MAIN"}Name mmu - MikMod Utilities @{" " link "'#toc1'/MAIN"}Synopsis @{"b"}mmu@{"ub"} @{"i"}command@{"ui"} [@{"i"}generaloptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}commandoptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}command arguments@{"ui"}] 
@{"b"}mmu --loaders@{"ub"} 
@{"b"}mmu --help@{"ub"} 
@{"b"}mmu --version@{"ub"} @{" " link "'#toc2'/MAIN"}Description MikMod Utilities is collection of command line tools for manipulating the module sound files that are typically produced by Soundtracker, Protracker and other tools. MikMod Utilities consists of the following tools: @{"b"}mmuinfo@{"ub"} gives information about module @{"b"}mmuplay@{"ub"} plays modules @{"b"}mmuplaysmp@{"ub"} plays samples from modules @{"b"}mmurender@{"ub"} converts modules to other audio formats @{"b"}mmurip@{"ub"} extracts samples from module @{"b"}mmutotal@{"ub"} computes total modules time 

If your system has support for the symbolic links, then there tools is available as appropriate commands. Otherwise its available only by passing @{"i"}command@{"ui"} to the @{"b"}mmu@{"ub"} executable. The @{"i"}command@{"ui"} is identical to the appropriate tool name with the "mmu" prefix removed. For examle, 

@{"b"}mmuinfo music.mod@{"ub"} 

is equivalent to: 

@{"b"}mmu info music.mod@{"ub"} 

All tools has support for the automatic modules decompression from bzip, gzip and pkzip archives, but this can be configured at compile-time and can be controlled at run-time. Also all tools, except @{"b"}mmutotal@{"ub"}, can load modules from standard input. 

MikMod Utilities uses MikMod Sound Library to load and play modules. So that MikMod Utilities can handle all module formats that supported by libmikmod. @{" " link "'#toc3'/MAIN"}Exit Status MikMod Utilities uses standard exit status, as defined in sysexits.h. The values used are: @{"b"}0@{"ub"} The command was successfully executed. @{"b"}64@{"ub"} The command was used incorrectly, e.g., with the wrong number of arguments, a bad flag, a bad syntax in a parameter, or whatever. @{"b"}65@{"ub"} The input data was incorrect, e.g. module format not supported or module is wrong. @{"b"}66@{"ub"} An input file did not exist or was not readable. @{"b"}70@{"ub"} An internal software error has been detected. @{"b"}71@{"ub"} An operating system error has been detected. @{"b"}73@{"ub"} A output file cannot be created. @{"b"}74@{"ub"} An error occurred while doing I/O on some file. @{" " link "'#toc4'/MAIN"}General Options @{"b"}--loaders@{"ub"} List module loaders. This may give information about supported module formats. @{"b"}--nodecompress@{"ub"} Disable automatic archives decompression. If the module file name that given in the @{"i"}command arguments@{"ui"} match pattern of one of supported archives formats, then automatic decompression is occur, this option disables this behavior. @{"b"}--bzip@{"ub"} Force bzip input decompression. This may be useful when bzip-compressed module are loaded from standard input. This option is available only if Bzip2 support is present. @{"b"}--gzip@{"ub"} Force gzip input decompression. This may be useful when gzip-compressed module are loaded from standard input. This option is available only if Zlib support is present. @{"b"}--pkzip@{"ub"} Force pkzip input decompression. This may be useful when pkzip-compressed module are loaded from standard input. This option is available only if Zlib support is present. @{"b"}--help@{"ub"} Display short command usage help and exit. @{"b"}--version@{"ub"} Display version information and exit. This will display also information about supported libraries and other compile-time configuration. @{" " link "'#toc5'/MAIN"}Bugs If you found any, please let me known. @{" " link "'#toc6'/MAIN"}Author Konstantin Korikov <lostclus@ua.fm> @{" " link "'#toc7'/MAIN"}See Also @{" " link "'mmuinfo.guide/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmuinfo(1) ,@{"ub"} @{" " link "'mmuplay.guide/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmuplay(1) ,@{"ub"} @{" " link "'mmuplaysmp.guide/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmuplaysmp(1) ,@{"ub"} @{" " link "'mmurender.guide/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmurender(1) ,@{"ub"} @{" " link "'mmurip.guide/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmurip(1) ,@{"ub"} @{" " link "'mmutotal.guide/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmutotal(1) ,@{"ub"} @{" " link "'mikmod.guide/MAIN"}@{"b"}mikmod(1)@{"ub"} 


